- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the architecture of quantum-classical computing and proposes a new model for it.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new software engineering approach for quantum-classical computing, which involves a new programming model and language extension.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions the best practices of high performance computing (HPC), which involves distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, and aims to build on those practices for quantum-classical computing.
